<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  @!component('components.head', title="Teacher Allocation System")
 
  <body>
    <div class="wrapper">
      @include('partials/sidebar')
      <div class="content-section">
    <section class="main-content">
      <h1 class="page-title">Help</h1>
      <h2 class="page-subtitle">A guide to using the Teaching Allocation System (TAS)</h2>
      
      <div class="dashboard-col">
        <div class="dashboard-card">

              <h2 class="dashboard-title">General</h2>

              <div class="table-static">
                <div class="table-section--xx-small text-align-center margin-8"><i class="fa fa-chevron-right" aria-hidden="true"></i></div>
                <div class="table-section--xx-large margin-8">Getting started</div>
              </div>
              <div class="table-collapse">
                <p>To start allocating, you can import a spreadsheet containing the details of academics and units. Make sure the file format is <b>.xlsx</b>.</p>
              </div>

              <div class="table-static">
                <div class="table-section--xx-small text-align-center margin-8"><i class="fa fa-chevron-right" aria-hidden="true"></i></div>
                <div class="table-section--xx-large margin-8">How do I add a tag?</div>
              </div>
              <div class="table-collapse">
                <p>You can assign tag(s) to allocations and academics.</p>
                <li>Click on the <b>Edit</b> button beside the allocation or academic you want to tag.</li>
                <li>In the <b>Tags</b> field, write a # followed by the tag you want to assign. For example, <b>#Security</b> <b>#Databases</b> <b>#Networks</b>.</li>
              </div>

              &nbsp<h2 class="dashboard-title">Using the Allocations page</h2>

              <div class="table-static">
                <div class="table-section--xx-small text-align-center margin-8"><i class="fa fa-chevron-right" aria-hidden="true"></i></div>
                <div class="table-section--xx-large margin-8">What do the table headings mean?</div>
              </div>
              <div class="table-collapse">
                <li><b>Name</b> -> The full name of the academic staff member.</li>
                <li><b>Preferred Load</b> -> The amount of work load the academic is comfortable doing in a semester.</li>
                <li><b>Actual Load</b> -> The amount of work load of all unit(s) assigned to the academic for a semester.</li>
                <li><b>Tags</b> -> A list of keyword(s) that categorise the allocation. It helps to filter categories when searching.</li>
                &nbsp<li><b>Status</b> -> A colour showing the relationship between the preferred load and the actual load of an academic. It can be one of three colours: red, yellow or green.
                <li>If the status is <u>red</u>, the actual load is more than the preferred load. It is suggested to reduce the number of unit(s) assigned to the academic.</li>
                <li>If the status is <u>yellow</u>, the actual load is less than the preferred load. The academic can be assigned to more unit(s).</li>
                <li>If the status is <u>green</u>, the actual load matches the preferred load. This is ideal for the academic.</li></li>
              </div>

              <div class="table-static">
                <div class="table-section--xx-small text-align-center margin-8"><i class="fa fa-chevron-right" aria-hidden="true"></i></div>
                <div class="table-section--xx-large margin-8">How do I search for an allocation?</div>
              </div>
              <div class="table-collapse">
                <li>To search for a particular allocation, type in the search bar.</li>
                <li>To <u>filter</u> allocations, choose from the <u>left drop down menu</u>. You can filter by year, status or tags.</li>
                <li>To <u>sort</u> allocations, choose from the <u>right drop down menu</u>. You can sort by year, preferred load, actual load, status or tags.</li>
                &nbsp<p>Once you are ready to perform the search, click the magnifying glass icon beside the search bar, or press <b>Enter</b> on your keyboard.</p>
              </div>

              <div class="table-static">
                <div class="table-section--xx-small text-align-center margin-8"><i class="fa fa-chevron-right" aria-hidden="true"></i></div>
                <div class="table-section--xx-large margin-8">How do I add an allocation?</div>
              </div>
              <div class="table-collapse">
                <li>Click the <b>Add Allocation +</b> button.</li>
                <li>Fill in the details. Mandatory fields are pre-filled.</li>
                <li>Once you are ready, click on the <b>Add Allocation</b> button.</li>
                &nbsp<p>The academic has been successfully allocated.</p>
              </div>

              &nbsp<h2 class="dashboard-title">Using the Academics page</h2>

              <div class="table-static">
                <div class="table-section--xx-small text-align-center margin-8"><i class="fa fa-chevron-right" aria-hidden="true"></i></div>
                <div class="table-section--xx-large margin-8">What do the table headings mean?</div>
              </div>
              <div class="table-collapse">
                <li><b>Name</b> -> The full name of the academic staff member.</li>
                <li><b>School</b> -> The area of study the academic works in.</li>
                <li><b>Load</b> -> The amount of work load of all unit(s) assigned to the academic for a semester.</li>
                <li><b>Academic Preference</b> -> </li>
                <li><b>Status</b> -> </li>
                <li><b>Tags</b> -> A list of keyword(s) that categorise the academic. It helps to filter categories when searching.</li>
              </div>

              <div class="table-static">
                <div class="table-section--xx-small text-align-center margin-8"><i class="fa fa-chevron-right" aria-hidden="true"></i></div>
                <div class="table-section--xx-large margin-8">How do I search for an academic?</div>
              </div>
              <div class="table-collapse">
                <li>To search for a particular academic, type in the search bar.</li>
                <li>To <u>filter</u> academics, choose from the <u>left drop down menu</u>. You can filter by year, status or tags.</li>
                <li>To <u>sort</u> academic, choose from the <u>right drop down menu</u>. You can sort by year, school, load, status or tags.</li>
                &nbsp<p>Once you are ready to perform the search, click the magnifying glass icon beside the search bar, or press <b>Enter</b> on your keyboard.</p>
              </div>

              <div class="table-static">
                <div class="table-section--xx-small text-align-center margin-8"><i class="fa fa-chevron-right" aria-hidden="true"></i></div>
                <div class="table-section--xx-large margin-8">How do I add an academic?</div>
              </div>
              <div class="table-collapse">
                <li>Click the <b>Add Academic +</b> button.</li>
                <li>Fill in the details. Mandatory fields are pre-filled.</li>
                <li>Once you are ready, click on the <b>Add Academic</b> button.</li>
                &nbsp<p>The academic has been successfully added to the database.</p>
              </div>

              &nbsp<h2 class="dashboard-title">Using the Units page</h2>

              <div class="table-static">
                <div class="table-section--xx-small text-align-center margin-8"><i class="fa fa-chevron-right" aria-hidden="true"></i></div>
                <div class="table-section--xx-large margin-8">What do the table headings mean?</div>
              </div>
              <div class="table-collapse">
                <li><b>ID</b> -> The unit code.</li>
                <li><b>Name</b> -> The name of the unit.</li>
                <li><b>Semester</b> -> The half of the year in which the unit is running. It can be semester 1 or 2, not both.</li>
                <li><b>Assigned Load</b> -> </li>
                <li><b>Status</b> -> </li>
              </div>

              <div class="table-static">
                <div class="table-section--xx-small text-align-center margin-8"><i class="fa fa-chevron-right" aria-hidden="true"></i></div>
                <div class="table-section--xx-large margin-8">How do I search for a unit?</div>
              </div>
              <div class="table-collapse">
                <li>To search for a particular unit, type in the search bar.</li>
                <li>To <u>filter</u> allocations, choose from the <u>left drop down menu</u>. You can filter by year, semester, assigned load or statuss.</li>
                <li>To <u>sort</u> allocations, choose from the <u>right drop down menu</u>. You can sort by year, ID, name, semester, assigned load, status or tags.</li>
                &nbsp<p>Once you are ready to perform the search, click the magnifying glass icon beside the search bar, or press <b>Enter</b> on your keyboard.</p>
              </div>

              <div class="table-static">
                <div class="table-section--xx-small text-align-center margin-8"><i class="fa fa-chevron-right" aria-hidden="true"></i></div>
                <div class="table-section--xx-large margin-8">How do I add a unit?</div>
              </div>
              <div class="table-collapse">
                <li>Click the <b>Add Unit +</b> button.</li>
                <li>Fill in the details. Mandatory fields are pre-filled.</li>
                <li>Once you are ready, click on the <b>Add Unit</b> button.</li>
                &nbsp<p>The unit has been successfully added to the database.</p>
                <p>If a unit goes for two semesters, add the unit twice. Choose semester 1 for the first one and semester 2 for the other.</p>
              </div>

              &nbsp<h2 class="dashboard-title">Importing and exporting</h2>

              <div class="table-static">
                <div class="table-section--xx-small text-align-center margin-8"><i class="fa fa-chevron-right" aria-hidden="true"></i></div>
                <div class="table-section--xx-large margin-8">How do I import a spreadsheet into TAS?</div>
              </div>
              <div class="table-collapse">
                <p>Before importing, make sure the file is an Excel spreadsheet in the format <b>.xlsx.</b></p>
                <li>Drag and drop the file, or
                <li>Select the spreadsheet from your local computer.</li>
                <li>Click the <b>Import</b> button.</li>
              </div>

              <div class="table-static">
                <div class="table-section--xx-small text-align-center margin-8"><i class="fa fa-chevron-right" aria-hidden="true"></i></div>
                <div class="table-section--xx-large margin-8">How do I export my allocations, academics and units?</div>
              </div>
              <div class="table-collapse">
                <p>You can export a spreadsheet of any allocations, academics and units you have added or edited in TAS.</p>
                <li>Choose a year from the drop down menu.</li>
                <li>Click the <b>Export</b> button.</li>
                <li>The file will now download as an Excel spreadsheet in the format <b>.xlsx</b>.</li>
              </div>

            </div>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
  </div>
    
  </body>
</html>

@!component('components.expandCollapse')
